## Agent communication

You may be running alongside other Claude Code agents in a shared tmux session. Use these commands to discover and communicate with peers:

- `peers` — list all active agents (slot, name, directory)
- `msg <slot_or_name> <message>` — send a message to a specific agent
- `broadcast <message>` — send a message to ALL other agents
- `whoami` — show your own slot, name, and directory

Use `peers` before messaging to get current slot numbers. Prefer name-based addressing (`msg flashback-cns "check the logs"`) over slot numbers when possible.

